physdesc.extent: A scrapbook compiled by Annie Whelen Jensen (Tailgate Annie)

did.abstract: This collections consists of one scrapbook created by Annie Whelen Jensen who owned a truck stop cafe in Chicago the 1930s and 1940s.
did.physloc: Materials may be stored off-site and may require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The material is arranged as it was originally compiled by Mrs. Jensen. Individual pages have been placed in mylar sleeves.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This scrapbook contains correspondence, clippings, photographs, and greeting cards, compiled by Annie Laurie Whelen Jensen. The scrapbook relates to Mrs. Jensen's time as proprieter of the Tailgate cafe in Chicago.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Annie Laurie Whelen Jensen was born August 21, 1910, in Farmington, Missouri. She worked as a waitress and a comedy wrestler before opening the Tailgate cafe in Chicago. After selling the cafe she and her husband moved to San Francisco. She died on October 14, 1954.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: This item was transferred from the International Brotherhood of Teamsters. It was originally donated to the Teamsters by Barbara L. Vondruska, Annie Jensens's niece.
